{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d6cc6f0d-9bd5-4064-bdba-fe0fd874c698","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key things to know:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.8 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform**, so just deleting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is enough.\n2. **`dotnet test`** works as before — no command changes needed.\n3. **`.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but VSTest-specific adapter settings may need updating.\n4. If you use **`vstest.console.exe` directly**, switch to `dotnet test` or run the test executable directly (`./MyTests.exe`).\n5. Review any CI scripts that parse VSTest-specific TRX output or use `/logger` flags — the platform uses `--report-trx` instead.\n\nRun `dotnet test` after the change to verify everything passes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1caa796e-f105-468a-92f8-6f590916670d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There's no relevant documentation in this repository. I'll answer from my knowledge about MSTest.Sdk and the migration from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.","outputTokens":383,"requestId":"5C2B:1077B7:A2B51:CC008:69F54AF0"},"id":"cb8c53b7-4677-4a5f-96aa-743f0f5ded94","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:53:13.945Z","parentId":"b4ff9db7-d31d-4c70-94cb-96cdb10e382e"}
